This paper is likely to belong to the Natural Language Processing (NLP) subfield of Computer Science, as it focuses on evaluating methods for learning word representations. Specifically, it deals with word embeddings, which are a popular technique in NLP for representing words as vectors in a high-dimensional space. 

cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category, as it specifically deals with NLP and its applications. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely, as word embeddings are a type of machine learning model. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category, as word embeddings are used in many AI applications, such as natural language understanding and machine translation. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category, as word embeddings are often learned using neural networks. 

cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a less likely sub-category, but still possible, as word embeddings can be used to improve information retrieval systems.
